description:
&lt;p&gt;It is an exciting time to be joining Surrey as we are transforming the way we deliver emotional wellbeing and mental health services to our children, young people and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surrey and Borders Partnership NHS Foundation Trust is the leading provider of health and social care services for people of all ages with mental ill health, drug and alcohol misuse, and learning disabilities in Surrey and north east Hampshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We deliver high quality care across our 140 services; to achieve this we employ 2,300 staff over 39 sites, serving a population of 1.3 million.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surrey CAMHS sees all young people, up to their 18th birthday, regardless of educational status. Working with a range of third sector and voluntary sector partners together with wider children’s system stakeholders we provide an extensive range of early intervention and specialist services which includes Community CAMHS teams, Children’s Eating Disorders, Learning Disability, Forensic Services and a range of services for Looked after Children and Children in Care. Our services for children and young people with complex and high risk needs includes nationally recognised Hope and Extended Hope Services. Additionally a range of Crisis Services including a Crisis Intervention Team and Children’s and Young People’s Haven’s ensure a comprehensive response to CYP in crisis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst our focus remains on early intervention and prevention and effective community CAMH services there are some children and young people who require specialist inpatient CAMHS provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As CAMHS Tier 4 Operational lead, you will play a key role in leading and overseeing the management of care between community and inpatient settings. We are looking for an individual with extensive experience of operationally leading services for children and young people with acute and complex care needs, comfortable working in a fast-paced environment requiring quick solutions, managing multiple stakeholders and driven by a strong passion and commitment to improve the emotional wellbeing of children, young people and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading the implementation and set up of a new Surrey CAMHS Tier 4 Management Hub on behalf of Surrey Heartland Integrated Care System.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsibility for developing and delivering all functions to oversee the safe management of all Surrey children requiring Tier 4 inpatient admission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Setting up systems to oversee clinical care and quality, financial oversight and budgetary management as well as contractual relationships and management of Tier 4 providers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Playing a key leading role in managing both external stakeholders (NHSE, Independent providers, Neighbouring PCS) and internal stakeholders (SABP, Social Care, Education, Acute’s, GP’s) to ensure the best quality of care for Surrey children and their families&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
